        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:57AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 556 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Apple Springs, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lufkin, Diboll, Hudson, Burke, Redland, Clawson, and Central.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
